16.7 We recommended to the management to submit the following documents, subject for audit:
The Annual Procurement Plan for the procurement of Fuel, Oil and Lubricants which stated the planned mode of procurement and/or supplemental APP for amendment/s;
The delegation of specific officials, personnel, committee or office in the Procuring Entity to conduct the Direct Retail Purchase; and
The terms and conditions or similar agreements submitted indicating the use of Direct Retail Purchase for the POL products between the LGU and supplier for the procurements as enumerated under Annex T.
Also, submit explanations/justifications on the following deficiencies:
Direct Retail Purchase of POL products found on the attached APP was only reported as “Monthly Quantity Requirement” and not for the fiscal year;
Attached Resolutions only recommended “Alternative Mode of Procurement -Single or Lowest Calculated and Responsive indicated in RFQ” without specifically identifying the alternative method to be used by the LGU;
Attached documents found incoherent with written inquiries as Purchase Orders stated “Small Value Procurement” contrary to the latter indicating “Direct Retail Purchase”;
The terms indicated under the Purchase Orders (PO) to deliver the POL products 15 calendar days from receipt of the PO which defeated the nature of the Direct Retail Purchase which is intended for non-bulk purchases. The Delivery Receipts, Invoices and Acceptance & Inspection reports also implied that the products were delivered and accepted in bulk;
There were still no consumption reports and other supporting documents for fuel consumption submitted as of the even date despite the terms indicated on the Purchase Orders (which were dated from February 16 to May 10, 2024) to deliver the said products just 15 calendar days from the receipt of the PO; and
A Collection Receipt for the whole contract amount was dated as fast as 9 calendar days from the Purchase Orders, and an Invoice was dated prior to PO, which may either indicate possible advance payments or the risks that the products were expended before undergoing proper procurement procedures.

