Segregation of waste as to biodegradable and non-biodegradable should be strictly followed by the residents and business establishments;
Issuance of citation tickets to solid waste violators;
Impose strict compliance on collection of biodegradable and non-biodegradable waste pursuant to Section 21 of R.A. 9003;
Strict imposition of “No Segregation, No Collection” Policy; and
Prevention of littering n public places.

Furthermore, we also recommended that the Municipal Engineering Office should ensure the proper and immediate construction of the Sanitary Landfill.

The management agreed with the recommendations. However, it was pointed out that waste segregation can only be fully implemented upon completion of their sanitary landfill.  Nonetheless, management assured the audit team that the Sanitary Landfill and MRF will be constructed in CY 2018. As of this writing, management has already begun the bidding process.

Recommendations:
We recommend that the Municipal Treasurer/Designated General Service Officer shall maintain property cards to be reconciled with the records of the Accounting Office. An Inventory Committee shall also be created to prioritize the conduct physical count of property, plant and equipment of the agency and to be able to prepare and submit the RPCPPE on or before January 31 of the following year.
We also recommend that the accounting office and the GSO shall reconcile regularly their records to determine the actual balances of PPE in order to present fairly the balances of the affected accounts at year-end. The balances in the RPCPPE and the accounting records should be investigated and adjusted accordingly;

We recommended the following:

The MTO must have copies of the Journal Entry Voucher related to Cash In Bank for easy reference and monitoring;
The MTO must prepare a “Report of Checks Issued” for each bank account of the LGU, done chronologically including cancelled/void check, in submitting the Disbursement Vouchers to the Municipal Accounting Office.
The MTO must submit all the paid the Disbursement Vouchers to the Municipal Accounting Office;
If possible, the MTO must submit all or completely the DVs corresponding the actual checks issued for each month.
